{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","platforms":[{"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"15.0","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"iOS"},{"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"macOS"},{"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"16.0","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"tvOS"},{"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"1.0","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"visionOS"},{"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"11.0","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"watchOS"}],"title":"OUDSSwitchItem","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSSwitchItem","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents14OUDSSwitchItemV","symbolKind":"struct","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSSwitchItem","kind":"identifier"}]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsswitchitem"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Switch item is a UI element that allows to toggle between two states, typically “On” and “Off”, and used to enable or disable features, options or settings."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Switch Item covers a wider range of contexts by allowing to toggle the visibility of additional text labels and icon assets."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSSwitchItem"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Layouts","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Layouts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"inverse"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": like the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" layout but with a trailing switch indicator and a leading optional decorative icon"}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Indicator-states","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Indicator states"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The switch indicator has two available states set as a boolean property that determines whether the toggle is on or off."}]},{"anchor":"Particular-cases","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Particular cases"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the ","type":"text"},{"code":"isError","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is risen."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition, the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem"},{"type":"text","text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet but this component must not be considered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as disabled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The switch can be also outlined in some cases."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","text":"Accessibility considerations","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}]},{"text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and optional texts and a custom switch trait.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Forbidden by design","anchor":"Forbidden-by-design"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component."}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component."}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component.","type":"text"}]}]},{"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Code samples"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an unselected state","    @Published var isOn: Bool = false","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn)","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label, and a description text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, description: \"The Beatles\")","","    \/\/ A leading switch with an additional label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, description: \"The Beatles\")","","    \/\/ A trailing switch with a label, an additonal label, a description text and an icon.","    \/\/ The inverse layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\",","                   isOn: $isOn,","                   description: \"The Beatles\",","                   isReversed: true,","                   icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"))","","    \/\/ A trailing switch with a label, a description text, an icon, a divider and is about an error.","    \/\/ The inverse layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Rescue from this world!\",","                   isOn: $isOn,","                   description: \"Put your hand in mine\",","                   icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"),","                   isReversed: true,","                   isError: true,","                   hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Rescue from this world!\",","                   isOn: $isOn,","                   isError: true,","                   errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                   hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Rescue from this world!\", isOn: $isOn)","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related switch as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Kaboom!\", isOn: $isOn, isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Kaboom!\", isOn: $isOn, isReadyOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, flipLeadingIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-switch"}]},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Themes rendering"},{"anchor":"Orange","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Orange"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_switchItem_Orange"}]},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Orange Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_switchItem_OrangeCompact"}]},{"anchor":"Sosh","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_switchItem_Sosh"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Wireframe","anchor":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_switchItem_Wireframe","type":"image"}]},{"name":"Version","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.5.0 (Figma component design version)"}]}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Since","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0.14.0","type":"text"}]}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc